Global Funds Buy Net 17.4 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-05-16T03:32:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/global-funds-buy-net-17-4-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 17.4
billion rupees ($386 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
May 13, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 1.3 percent to 1 trillion rupees, or 36.2
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds sold a net 1.61 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on May 13, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
